Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
colorizePowerMesh(25.10)                              colorizePowerMesh(25.10)

Name
       colorizePowerMesh

Syntax
       colorizePowerMesh

       [-help] [-reverse_with_nondefault_width {0 | 1}]

       Use  this  command  to  colorize (assign mask information) power struc-
       tures, including power wires and power  via  metals,  in  multi-pattern
       layers.  This  command  also fixes color violations of power metals in-
       cluding via metals. It is recommended to use this command once all  the
       power  meshes  are built. This command honors the FIXEDMASKS keyword in
       the LEF of the cell, in the case of colored LEF.

       Note:

              * This command colors only the PG wires and  PG  via  enclosure.
                but  not  the  PG  via cut. Also, it does not color pre-routed
                signal nets. All signal  nets  are  colored  while  using  the
                place_opt_design or routeDesign command.

              * The  command  does not fix via cut colors. To fix cut color or
                trim cut with violation, use the fixVia command. This  command
                requires  correct  node setting in setDesignMode -process/set-
                NanoRouteMode -route_process_node.

              * The wide NDR wires will be assigned  with  a  different  color
                than the track color through this command.

Parameter
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each colorizePowerMesh parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man colorizePowerMesh

       -reverse_with_nondefault_width {0 | 1}
              Reverses the 'on track' wire color to the different 'from track'
              color, when the wire width is not the default width.

Related Information
              * Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

              * fixVia

              * setDesignMode

              * setNanoRouteMode

